</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35D6553FF88FF8DAE34F8D47D69F801" pageId="2" pageNumber="591" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BF836D8FF88FF8DAE34F8D47D69F801" blockId="2.[90,1299,292,2065]" pageId="2" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="B933EACAFF88FF8DAE34F8D47FAEF88B" bold="true" box="[92,449,1873,1902]" pageId="2" pageNumber="591">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List (under 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D5BFF88FF8DAE34F8F17F6FF870" baseAuthorityName="Shaw" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[92,256,1908,1941]" class="Mammalia" family="Acrobatidae" genus="Acrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="2" pageNumber="591" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">A. pygmaeus</taxonomicName>
). Recently collected museum voucher specimens of the Broad-toed Feather-tailed Glider document its continued survival across large parts ofits distribution and its occurrence in numerous protected areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
